title: Tim Keenan III Selected to SEC Community Service Team
text:
Tim Keenan III Selected to SEC Community Service Team
12/5/2024 9:06:00 AM | Football
The redshirt junior has maintained an attitude of service before self in his four seasons in Tuscaloosa
BIRMINGHAM, Ala. â€“ Alabama defensive lineman Tim Keenan III was selected to the 2024 Southeastern Conference Community Service Team, the league office announced Thursday.
The SEC names a Community Service Team for its 22-league sponsored sports, aiming to highlight a student-athlete from each school who gives back to his community through superior service efforts.
SEC Community Service Team
Tim Keenan III, Defensive Lineman
- Has logged nearly triple-digit volunteer hours since joining the Crimson Tide
- Keenan III's community service includes numerous events in Tuscaloosa and his hometown of Birmingham
- A mainstay at all Alabama team service events, including Habitat for Humanity builds
- Regularly volunteers with the Big Brothers, Big Sisters program in Tuscaloosa
- Hosted a free youth football clinic in Birmingham during the summer of 2024
- That same summer, Keenan III received a proclamation from the Mayor of Tuscaloosa for his work locally
